2361 tp->packets_out);
2362 }
2363#endif
2364}
2365#else
2366#define DBGUNDO(x...) do { } while (0)
2367#endif
2368
2369static void tcp_undo_cwnd_reduction(struct sock *sk, bool unmark_loss)
2370{
2371 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
2372
2373 if (unmark_loss) {
2374 struct sk_buff *skb;
2375
2376 tcp_for_write_queue(skb, sk) {
2377 if (skb == tcp_send_head(sk))
2378 break;
2379 TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->sacked &= ~TCPCB_LOST;
2380 }
2381 tp->lost_out = 0;
2382 tcp_clear_all_retrans_hints(tp);
2383 }
2384
2385 if (tp->prior_ssthresh) {
2386 const struct inet_connection_sock *icsk = inet_csk(sk);
2387
2388 tp->snd_cwnd = icsk->icsk_ca_ops->undo_cwnd(sk);
2389
2390 if (tp->prior_ssthresh > tp->snd_ssthresh) {
2391 tp->snd_ssthresh = tp->prior_ssthresh;
2392 tcp_ecn_withdraw_cwr(tp);
2393 }
2394 }
2395 tp->snd_cwnd_stamp = tcp_jiffies32;
2396 tp->undo_marker = 0;
2397}
2398
2399static inline bool tcp_may_undo(const struct tcp_sock *tp)
2400{
2401 return tp->undo_marker && (!tp->undo_retrans || tcp_packet_delayed(tp));
2402}
2403
2404/* People celebrate: "We love our President!" */
2405static bool tcp_try_undo_recovery(struct sock *sk)
2406{
2407 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
2408
2409 if (tcp_may_undo(tp)) {
2410 int mib_idx;
2411
2412 /* Happy end! We did not retransmit anything
2413 * or our original transmission succeeded.
2414 */
2415 DBGUNDO(sk, inet_csk(sk)->icsk_ca_state == TCP_CA_Loss ? "loss" : "retrans");
2416 tcp_undo_cwnd_reduction(sk, false);
2417 if (inet_csk(sk)->icsk_ca_state == TCP_CA_Loss)
2418 mib_idx = LINUX_MIB_TCPLOSSUNDO;
2419 else
2420 mib_idx = LINUX_MIB_TCPFULLUNDO;
2421
2422 NET_INC_STATS(sock_net(sk), mib_idx);
2423 }
2424 if (tp->snd_una == tp->high_seq && tcp_is_reno(tp)) {
2425 /* Hold old state until something *above* high_seq
2426 * is ACKed. For Reno it is MUST to prevent false
2427 * fast retransmits (RFC2582). SACK TCP is safe. */
2428 if (!tcp_any_retrans_done(sk))
2429 tp->retrans_stamp = 0;
2430 return true;
2431 }
2432 tcp_set_ca_state(sk, TCP_CA_Open);
2433 tp->is_sack_reneg = 0;
2434 return false;
2435}
2436
2437/* Try to undo cwnd reduction, because D-SACKs acked all retransmitted data */
2438static bool tcp_try_undo_dsack(struct sock *sk)
2439{
2440 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
2441
2442 if (tp->undo_marker && !tp->undo_retrans) {
2443 DBGUNDO(sk, "D-SACK");
2444 tcp_undo_cwnd_reduction(sk, false);
2445 NET_INC_STATS(sock_net(sk), LINUX_MIB_TCPDSACKUNDO);
2446 return true;
2447 }
2448 return false;
2449}
2450
2451/* Undo during loss recovery after partial ACK or using F-RTO. */
2452static bool tcp_try_undo_loss(struct sock *sk, bool frto_undo)
2453{
2454 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
2455
2456 if (frto_undo || tcp_may_undo(tp)) {
2457 tcp_undo_cwnd_reduction(sk, true);
2458
2459 DBGUNDO(sk, "partial loss");
2460 NET_INC_STATS(sock_net(sk), LINUX_MIB_TCPLOSSUNDO);
2461 if (frto_undo)
2462 NET_INC_STATS(sock_net(sk),
2463 LINUX_MIB_TCPSPURIOUSRTOS);
2464 inet_csk(sk)->icsk_retransmits = 0;
2465 if (frto_undo || tcp_is_sack(tp)) {
2466 tcp_set_ca_state(sk, TCP_CA_Open);
2467 tp->is_sack_reneg = 0;
2468 }
2469 return true;
2470 }
2471 return false;
2472}
2473
2474/* The cwnd reduction in CWR and Recovery uses the PRR algorithm in RFC 6937.
2475 * It computes the number of packets to send (sndcnt) based on packets newly
2476 * delivered:
2477 * 1) If the packets in flight is larger than ssthresh, PRR spreads the
2478 * cwnd reductions across a full RTT.
2479 * 2) Otherwise PRR uses packet conservation to send as much as delivered.
2480 * But when the retransmits are acked without further losses, PRR
2481 * slow starts cwnd up to ssthresh to speed up the recovery.
2482 */
2483static void tcp_init_cwnd_reduction(struct sock *sk)
2484{
2485 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
2486
2487 tp->high_seq = tp->snd_nxt;
2488 tp->tlp_high_seq = 0;
2489 tp->snd_cwnd_cnt = 0;
2490 tp->prior_cwnd = tp->snd_cwnd;
2491 tp->prr_delivered = 0;
2492 tp->prr_out = 0;
2493 tp->snd_ssthresh = inet_csk(sk)->icsk_ca_ops->ssthresh(sk);
2494 tcp_ecn_queue_cwr(tp);
2495}
2496
2497void tcp_cwnd_reduction(struct sock *sk, int newly_acked_sacked, int flag)
2498{
2499 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
2500 int sndcnt = 0;
2501 int delta = tp->snd_ssthresh - tcp_packets_in_flight(tp);
2502
2503 if (newly_acked_sacked <= 0 || WARN_ON_ONCE(!tp->prior_cwnd))
2504 return;
2505
2506 tp->prr_delivered += newly_acked_sacked;
2507 if (delta < 0) {
2508 u64 dividend = (u64)tp->snd_ssthresh * tp->prr_delivered +
2509 tp->prior_cwnd - 1;
2510 sndcnt = div_u64(dividend, tp->prior_cwnd) - tp->prr_out;
2511 } else if ((flag & FLAG_RETRANS_DATA_ACKED) &&
2512 !(flag & FLAG_LOST_RETRANS)) {
2513 sndcnt = min_t(int, delta,
2514 max_t(int, tp->prr_delivered - tp->prr_out,
2515 newly_acked_sacked) + 1);
2516 } else {
2517 sndcnt = min(delta, newly_acked_sacked);
2518 }
2519 /* Force a fast retransmit upon entering fast recovery */
2520 sndcnt = max(sndcnt, (tp->prr_out ? 0 : 1));
2521 tp->snd_cwnd = tcp_packets_in_flight(tp) + sndcnt;
2522}
2523
2524static inline void tcp_end_cwnd_reduction(struct sock *sk)
2525{
2526 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
2527
2528 if (inet_csk(sk)->icsk_ca_ops->cong_control)
2529 return;
2530
2531 /* Reset cwnd to ssthresh in CWR or Recovery (unless it's undone) */
2532 if (tp->snd_ssthresh < TCP_INFINITE_SSTHRESH &&
2533 (inet_csk(sk)->icsk_ca_state == TCP_CA_CWR || tp->undo_marker)) {
2534 tp->snd_cwnd = tp->snd_ssthresh;
2535 tp->snd_cwnd_stamp = tcp_jiffies32;
2536 }
2537 tcp_ca_event(sk, CA_EVENT_COMPLETE_CWR);
2538}
2539
2540/* Enter CWR state. Disable cwnd undo since congestion is proven with ECN */
2541void tcp_enter_cwr(struct sock *sk)
2542{
2543 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
2544
2545 tp->prior_ssthresh = 0;
2546 if (inet_csk(sk)->icsk_ca_state < TCP_CA_CWR) {
2547 tp->undo_marker = 0;
2548 tcp_init_cwnd_reduction(sk);
2549 tcp_set_ca_state(sk, TCP_CA_CWR);
2550 }
2551}
2552EXPORT_SYMBOL(tcp_enter_cwr);
2553
2554static void tcp_try_keep_open(struct sock *sk)
2555{
2556 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
2557 int state = TCP_CA_Open;
2558
2559 if (tcp_left_out(tp) || tcp_any_retrans_done(sk))
2560 state = TCP_CA_Disorder;
2561
2562 if (inet_csk(sk)->icsk_ca_state != state) {
2563 tcp_set_ca_state(sk, state);
2564 tp->high_seq = tp->snd_nxt;
2565 }
2566}
2567
2568static void tcp_try_to_open(struct sock *sk, int flag)
2569{
2570 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
2571
2572 tcp_verify_left_out(tp);
2573
2574 if (!tcp_any_retrans_done(sk))
2575 tp->retrans_stamp = 0;
2576
2577 if (flag & FLAG_ECE)
2578 tcp_enter_cwr(sk);
2579
2580 if (inet_csk(sk)->icsk_ca_state != TCP_CA_CWR) {
2581 tcp_try_keep_open(sk);
2582 }
2583}
2584
2585static void tcp_mtup_probe_failed(struct sock *sk)
2586{
2587 struct inet_connection_sock *icsk = inet_csk(sk);
2588
2589 icsk->icsk_mtup.search_high = icsk->icsk_mtup.probe_size - 1;
2590 icsk->icsk_mtup.probe_size = 0;
2591 NET_INC_STATS(sock_net(sk), LINUX_MIB_TCPMTUPFAIL);
2592}
2593
2594static void tcp_mtup_probe_success(struct sock *sk)
2595{
2596 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
2597 struct inet_connection_sock *icsk = inet_csk(sk);
2598
2599 /* FIXME: breaks with very large cwnd */
2600 tp->prior_ssthresh = tcp_current_ssthresh(sk);
2601 tp->snd_cwnd = tp->snd_cwnd *
2602 tcp_mss_to_mtu(sk, tp->mss_cache) /
2603 icsk->icsk_mtup.probe_size;
2604 tp->snd_cwnd_cnt = 0;
2605 tp->snd_cwnd_stamp = tcp_jiffies32;
2606 tp->snd_ssthresh = tcp_current_ssthresh(sk);
2607
2608 icsk->icsk_mtup.search_low = icsk->icsk_mtup.probe_size;
2609 icsk->icsk_mtup.probe_size = 0;
2610 tcp_sync_mss(sk, icsk->icsk_pmtu_cookie);
2611 NET_INC_STATS(sock_net(sk), LINUX_MIB_TCPMTUPSUCCESS);
2612}
2613
2614/* Do a simple retransmit without using the backoff mechanisms in
2615 * tcp_timer. This is used for path mtu discovery.
2616 * The socket is already locked here.
2617 */
2618void tcp_simple_retransmit(struct sock *sk)
2619{
2620 const struct inet_connection_sock *icsk = inet_csk(sk);
2621 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
2622 struct sk_buff *skb;
2623 unsigned int mss = tcp_current_mss(sk);
2624
2625 tcp_for_write_queue(skb, sk) {
2626 if (skb == tcp_send_head(sk))
2627 break;
2628 if (tcp_skb_seglen(skb) > mss &&
2629 !(TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->sacked & TCPCB_SACKED_ACKED)) {
2630 if (TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->sacked & TCPCB_SACKED_RETRANS) {
2631 TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->sacked &= ~TCPCB_SACKED_RETRANS;
2632 tp->retrans_out -= tcp_skb_pcount(skb);
2633 }
2634 tcp_skb_mark_lost_uncond_verify(tp, skb);
2635 }
2636 }
2637
2638 tcp_clear_retrans_hints_partial(tp);
2639
2640 if (!tp->lost_out)
2641 return;
2642
2643 if (tcp_is_reno(tp))
2644 tcp_limit_reno_sacked(tp);
2645
2646 tcp_verify_left_out(tp);
2647
2648 /* Don't muck with the congestion window here.
2649 * Reason is that we do not increase amount of _data_
2650 * in network, but units changed and effective
2651 * cwnd/ssthresh really reduced now.
2652 */
2653 if (icsk->icsk_ca_state != TCP_CA_Loss) {
2654 tp->high_seq = tp->snd_nxt;
2655 tp->snd_ssthresh = tcp_current_ssthresh(sk);
2656 tp->prior_ssthresh = 0;
2657 tp->undo_marker = 0;
2658 tcp_set_ca_state(sk, TCP_CA_Loss);
2659 }
2660 tcp_xmit_retransmit_queue(sk);
2661}
2662EXPORT_SYMBOL(tcp_simple_retransmit);
2663
2664void tcp_enter_recovery(struct sock *sk, bool ece_ack)
2665{
2666 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
2667 int mib_idx;
2668
2669 if (tcp_is_reno(tp))
2670 mib_idx = LINUX_MIB_TCPRENORECOVERY;
2671 else
2672 mib_idx = LINUX_MIB_TCPSACKRECOVERY;
2673
2674 NET_INC_STATS(sock_net(sk), mib_idx);
2675
2676 tp->prior_ssthresh = 0;
2677 tcp_init_undo(tp);
2678
2679 if (!tcp_in_cwnd_reduction(sk)) {
2680 if (!ece_ack)
2681 tp->prior_ssthresh = tcp_current_ssthresh(sk);
2682 tcp_init_cwnd_reduction(sk);
2683 }
2684 tcp_set_ca_state(sk, TCP_CA_Recovery);
2685}
2686
2687/* Process an ACK in CA_Loss state. Move to CA_Open if lost data are
2688 * recovered or spurious. Otherwise retransmits more on partial ACKs.
2689 */
2690static void tcp_process_loss(struct sock *sk, int flag, bool is_dupack,
2691 int *rexmit)
2692{
2693 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
2694 bool recovered = !before(tp->snd_una, tp->high_seq);
2695
2696 if ((flag & FLAG_SND_UNA_ADVANCED) &&
2697 tcp_try_undo_loss(sk, false))
2698 return;
2699
2700 if (tp->frto) { /* F-RTO RFC5682 sec 3.1 (sack enhanced version). */
2701 /* Step 3.b. A timeout is spurious if not all data are
2702 * lost, i.e., never-retransmitted data are (s)acked.
2703 */
2704 if ((flag & FLAG_ORIG_SACK_ACKED) &&
2705 tcp_try_undo_loss(sk, true))
2706 return;
2707
2708 if (after(tp->snd_nxt, tp->high_seq)) {
2709 if (flag & FLAG_DATA_SACKED || is_dupack)
2710 tp->frto = 0; /* Step 3.a. loss was real */
2711 } else if (flag & FLAG_SND_UNA_ADVANCED && !recovered) {
2712 tp->high_seq = tp->snd_nxt;
2713 /* Step 2.b. Try send new data (but deferred until cwnd
2714 * is updated in tcp_ack()). Otherwise fall back to
2715 * the conventional recovery.
2716 */
2717 if (tcp_send_head(sk) &&
2718 after(tcp_wnd_end(tp), tp->snd_nxt)) {
2719 *rexmit = REXMIT_NEW;
2720 return;
2721 }
2722 tp->frto = 0;
2723 }
2724 }
2725
2726 if (recovered) {
2727 /* F-RTO RFC5682 sec 3.1 step 2.a and 1st part of step 3.a */
2728 tcp_try_undo_recovery(sk);
2729 return;
2730 }
2731 if (tcp_is_reno(tp)) {
2732 /* A Reno DUPACK means new data in F-RTO step 2.b above are
2733 * delivered. Lower inflight to clock out (re)tranmissions.
2734 */
2735 if (after(tp->snd_nxt, tp->high_seq) && is_dupack)
2736 tcp_add_reno_sack(sk);
2737 else if (flag & FLAG_SND_UNA_ADVANCED)
2738 tcp_reset_reno_sack(tp);
2739 }
2740 *rexmit = REXMIT_LOST;
2741}
2742
2743/* Undo during fast recovery after partial ACK. */
2744static bool tcp_try_undo_partial(struct sock *sk, const int acked)
2745{
2746 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
2747
2748 if (tp->undo_marker && tcp_packet_delayed(tp)) {
2749 /* Plain luck! Hole if filled with delayed
2750 * packet, rather than with a retransmit.
2751 */
2752 tcp_update_reordering(sk, tcp_fackets_out(tp) + acked, 1);
2753
2754 /* We are getting evidence that the reordering degree is higher
2755 * than we realized. If there are no retransmits out then we
2756 * can undo. Otherwise we clock out new packets but do not
2757 * mark more packets lost or retransmit more.
2758 */
2759 if (tp->retrans_out)
2760 return true;
2761
2762 if (!tcp_any_retrans_done(sk))
2763 tp->retrans_stamp = 0;
2764
2765 DBGUNDO(sk, "partial recovery");
2766 tcp_undo_cwnd_reduction(sk, true);
2767 NET_INC_STATS(sock_net(sk), LINUX_MIB_TCPPARTIALUNDO);
2768 tcp_try_keep_open(sk);
2769 return true;
2770 }
2771 return false;
2772}
2773
2774static void tcp_rack_identify_loss(struct sock *sk, int *ack_flag)
2775{
2776 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
2777
2778 /* Use RACK to detect loss */
2779 if (sysctl_tcp_recovery & TCP_RACK_LOSS_DETECTION) {
2780 u32 prior_retrans = tp->retrans_out;
2781
2782 tcp_rack_mark_lost(sk);
2783 if (prior_retrans > tp->retrans_out)
2784 *ack_flag |= FLAG_LOST_RETRANS;
2785 }
2786}
2787
2788/* Process an event, which can update packets-in-flight not trivially.
2789 * Main goal of this function is to calculate new estimate for left_out,
2790 * taking into account both packets sitting in receiver's buffer and
2791 * packets lost by network.
2792 *
2793 * Besides that it updates the congestion state when packet loss or ECN
2794 * is detected. But it does not reduce the cwnd, it is done by the
2795 * congestion control later.
2796 *
2797 * It does _not_ decide what to send, it is made in function
2798 * tcp_xmit_retransmit_queue().
2799 */
2800static void tcp_fastretrans_alert(struct sock *sk, const int acked,
2801 bool is_dupack, int *ack_flag, int *rexmit)
2802{
2803 struct inet_connection_sock *icsk = inet_csk(sk);
2804 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
2805 int fast_rexmit = 0, flag = *ack_flag;
2806 bool do_lost = is_dupack || ((flag & FLAG_DATA_SACKED) &&
2807 (tcp_fackets_out(tp) > tp->reordering));
2808
2809 if (WARN_ON(!tp->packets_out && tp->sacked_out))
2810 tp->sacked_out = 0;
2811 if (WARN_ON(!tp->sacked_out && tp->fackets_out))
2812 tp->fackets_out = 0;
2813
2814 /* Now state machine starts.
2815 * A. ECE, hence prohibit cwnd undoing, the reduction is required. */
2816 if (flag & FLAG_ECE)
2817 tp->prior_ssthresh = 0;
2818
2819 /* B. In all the states check for reneging SACKs. */
2820 if (tcp_check_sack_reneging(sk, flag))
2821 return;
2822
2823 /* C. Check consistency of the current state. */
2824 tcp_verify_left_out(tp);
2825
2826 /* D. Check state exit conditions. State can be terminated
2827 * when high_seq is ACKed. */
2828 if (icsk->icsk_ca_state == TCP_CA_Open) {
2829 WARN_ON(tp->retrans_out != 0);
2830 tp->retrans_stamp = 0;
2831 } else if (!before(tp->snd_una, tp->high_seq)) {
2832 switch (icsk->icsk_ca_state) {
2833 case TCP_CA_CWR:
2834 /* CWR is to be held something *above* high_seq
2835 * is ACKed for CWR bit to reach receiver. */
2836 if (tp->snd_una != tp->high_seq) {
2837 tcp_end_cwnd_reduction(sk);
2838 tcp_set_ca_state(sk, TCP_CA_Open);
2839 }
2840 break;
2841
2842 case TCP_CA_Recovery:
2843 if (tcp_is_reno(tp))
2844 tcp_reset_reno_sack(tp);
2845 if (tcp_try_undo_recovery(sk))
2846 return;
2847 tcp_end_cwnd_reduction(sk);
2848 break;
2849 }
2850 }
2851
2852 /* E. Process state. */
2853 switch (icsk->icsk_ca_state) {
2854 case TCP_CA_Recovery:
2855 if (!(flag & FLAG_SND_UNA_ADVANCED)) {
2856 if (tcp_is_reno(tp) && is_dupack)
2857 tcp_add_reno_sack(sk);
2858 } else {
2859 if (tcp_try_undo_partial(sk, acked))
2860 return;
2861 /* Partial ACK arrived. Force fast retransmit. */
2862 do_lost = tcp_is_reno(tp) ||
2863 tcp_fackets_out(tp) > tp->reordering;
2864 }
2865 if (tcp_try_undo_dsack(sk)) {
2866 tcp_try_keep_open(sk);
2867 return;
2868 }
2869 tcp_rack_identify_loss(sk, ack_flag);
2870 break;
2871 case TCP_CA_Loss:
2872 tcp_process_loss(sk, flag, is_dupack, rexmit);
2873 tcp_rack_identify_loss(sk, ack_flag);
2874 if (!(icsk->icsk_ca_state == TCP_CA_Open ||
2875 (*ack_flag & FLAG_LOST_RETRANS)))
2876 return;
2877 /* Change state if cwnd is undone or retransmits are lost */
2878 default:
2879 if (tcp_is_reno(tp)) {
2880 if (flag & FLAG_SND_UNA_ADVANCED)
2881 tcp_reset_reno_sack(tp);
2882 if (is_dupack)
2883 tcp_add_reno_sack(sk);
2884 }
2885
2886 if (icsk->icsk_ca_state <= TCP_CA_Disorder)
2887 tcp_try_undo_dsack(sk);
2888
2889 tcp_rack_identify_loss(sk, ack_flag);
2890 if (!tcp_time_to_recover(sk, flag)) {
2891 tcp_try_to_open(sk, flag);
2892 return;
2893 }
2894
2895 /* MTU probe failure: don't reduce cwnd */
2896 if (icsk->icsk_ca_state < TCP_CA_CWR &&
2897 icsk->icsk_mtup.probe_size &&
2898 tp->snd_una == tp->mtu_probe.probe_seq_start) {
2899 tcp_mtup_probe_failed(sk);
2900 /* Restores the reduction we did in tcp_mtup_probe() */
2901 tp->snd_cwnd++;
2902 tcp_simple_retransmit(sk);
2903 return;
2904 }
2905
2906 /* Otherwise enter Recovery state */
2907 tcp_enter_recovery(sk, (flag & FLAG_ECE));
2908 fast_rexmit = 1;
2909 }
2910
2911 if (do_lost)
2912 tcp_update_scoreboard(sk, fast_rexmit);
2913 *rexmit = REXMIT_LOST;
2914}
2915
2916static void tcp_update_rtt_min(struct sock *sk, u32 rtt_us)
2917{
2918 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
2919 u32 wlen = sysctl_tcp_min_rtt_wlen * HZ;
2920
2921 minmax_running_min(&tp->rtt_min, wlen, tcp_jiffies32,
2922 rtt_us ? : jiffies_to_usecs(1));
2923}
2924
2925static bool tcp_ack_update_rtt(struct sock *sk, const int flag,
2926 long seq_rtt_us, long sack_rtt_us,
2927 long ca_rtt_us, struct rate_sample *rs)
2928{
2929 const struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
2930
2931 /* Prefer RTT measured from ACK's timing to TS-ECR. This is because
2932 * broken middle-boxes or peers may corrupt TS-ECR fields. But
2933 * Karn's algorithm forbids taking RTT if some retransmitted data
2934 * is acked (RFC6298).
2935 */
2936 if (seq_rtt_us < 0)
2937 seq_rtt_us = sack_rtt_us;
2938
2939 /* RTTM Rule: A TSecr value received in a segment is used to
2940 * update the averaged RTT measurement only if the segment
2941 * acknowledges some new data, i.e., only if it advances the
2942 * left edge of the send window.
2943 * See draft-ietf-tcplw-high-performance-00, section 3.3.
2944 */
2945 if (seq_rtt_us < 0 && tp->rx_opt.saw_tstamp && tp->rx_opt.rcv_tsecr &&
2946 flag & FLAG_ACKED) {
2947 u32 delta = tcp_time_stamp(tp) - tp->rx_opt.rcv_tsecr;
2948 u32 delta_us = delta * (USEC_PER_SEC / TCP_TS_HZ);
2949
2950 seq_rtt_us = ca_rtt_us = delta_us;
2951 }
2952 rs->rtt_us = ca_rtt_us; /* RTT of last (S)ACKed packet (or -1) */
2953 if (seq_rtt_us < 0)
2954 return false;
2955
2956 /* ca_rtt_us >= 0 is counting on the invariant that ca_rtt_us is
2957 * always taken together with ACK, SACK, or TS-opts. Any negative
2958 * values will be skipped with the seq_rtt_us < 0 check above.
2959 */
2960 tcp_update_rtt_min(sk, ca_rtt_us);
2961 tcp_rtt_estimator(sk, seq_rtt_us);
2962 tcp_set_rto(sk);
2963
2964 /* RFC6298: only reset backoff on valid RTT measurement. */
2965 inet_csk(sk)->icsk_backoff = 0;
2966 return true;
2967}
2968
2969/* Compute time elapsed between (last) SYNACK and the ACK completing 3WHS. */
2970void tcp_synack_rtt_meas(struct sock *sk, struct request_sock *req)
2971{
2972 struct rate_sample rs;
2973 long rtt_us = -1L;
2974
2975 if (req && !req->num_retrans && tcp_rsk(req)->snt_synack)
2976 rtt_us = tcp_stamp_us_delta(tcp_clock_us(), tcp_rsk(req)->snt_synack);
2977
2978 tcp_ack_update_rtt(sk, FLAG_SYN_ACKED, rtt_us, -1L, rtt_us, &rs);
2979}

2990/* Restart timer after forward progress on connection.
2991 * RFC2988 recommends to restart timer to now+rto.
2992 */
2993void tcp_rearm_rto(struct sock *sk)
2994{
2995 const struct inet_connection_sock *icsk = inet_csk(sk);
2996 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
2997
2998 /* If the retrans timer is currently being used by Fast Open
2999 * for SYN-ACK retrans purpose, stay put.
3000 */
3001 if (tp->fastopen_rsk)
3002 return;
3003
3004 if (!tp->packets_out) {
3005 inet_csk_clear_xmit_timer(sk, ICSK_TIME_RETRANS);
3006 } else {
3007 u32 rto = inet_csk(sk)->icsk_rto;
3008 /* Offset the time elapsed after installing regular RTO */
3009 if (icsk->icsk_pending == ICSK_TIME_REO_TIMEOUT ||
3010 icsk->icsk_pending == ICSK_TIME_LOSS_PROBE) {
3011 s64 delta_us = tcp_rto_delta_us(sk);
3012 /* delta_us may not be positive if the socket is locked
3013 * when the retrans timer fires and is rescheduled.
3014 */
3015 rto = usecs_to_jiffies(max_t(int, delta_us, 1));
3016 }
3017 inet_csk_reset_xmit_timer(sk, ICSK_TIME_RETRANS, rto,
3018 TCP_RTO_MAX);
3019 }
3020}
3021
3022/* Try to schedule a loss probe; if that doesn't work, then schedule an RTO. */
3023static void tcp_set_xmit_timer(struct sock *sk)
3024{
3025 if (!tcp_schedule_loss_probe(sk, true))
3026 tcp_rearm_rto(sk);
3027}

3029/* If we get here, the whole TSO packet has not been acked. */
3030static u32 tcp_tso_acked(struct sock *sk, struct sk_buff *skb)
3031{
3032 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
3033 u32 packets_acked;
3034
3035 BUG_ON(!after(TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->end_seq, tp->snd_una));
3036
3037 packets_acked = tcp_skb_pcount(skb);
3038 if (tcp_trim_head(sk, skb, tp->snd_una - TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->seq))
3039 return 0;
3040 packets_acked -= tcp_skb_pcount(skb);
3041
3042 if (packets_acked) {
3043 BUG_ON(tcp_skb_pcount(skb) == 0);
3044 BUG_ON(!before(TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->seq, TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->end_seq));
3045 }
3046
3047 return packets_acked;
3048}

3050static void tcp_ack_tstamp(struct sock *sk, struct sk_buff *skb,
3051 u32 prior_snd_una)
3052{
3053 const struct skb_shared_info *shinfo;
3054
3055 /* Avoid cache line misses to get skb_shinfo() and shinfo->tx_flags */
3056 if (likely(!TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->txstamp_ack))
3057 return;
3058
3059 shinfo = skb_shinfo(skb);
3060 if (!before(shinfo->tskey, prior_snd_una) &&
3061 before(shinfo->tskey, tcp_sk(sk)->snd_una))
3062 __skb_tstamp_tx(skb, NULL, sk, SCM_TSTAMP_ACK);
3063}
3064
3065/* Remove acknowledged frames from the retransmission queue. If our packet
3066 * is before the ack sequence we can discard it as it's confirmed to have
3067 * arrived at the other end.
3068 */
3069static int tcp_clean_rtx_queue(struct sock *sk, int prior_fackets,
3070 u32 prior_snd_una, int *acked,
3071 struct tcp_sacktag_state *sack)
3072{
3073 const struct inet_connection_sock *icsk = inet_csk(sk);
3074 u64 first_ackt, last_ackt;
3075 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
3076 u32 prior_sacked = tp->sacked_out;
3077 u32 reord = tp->packets_out;
3078 bool fully_acked = true;
3079 long sack_rtt_us = -1L;
3080 long seq_rtt_us = -1L;
3081 long ca_rtt_us = -1L;
3082 struct sk_buff *skb;
3083 u32 pkts_acked = 0;
3084 u32 last_in_flight = 0;
3085 bool rtt_update;
3086 int flag = 0;
3087
3088 first_ackt = 0;
3089
3090 while ((skb = tcp_write_queue_head(sk)) && skb != tcp_send_head(sk)) {
3091 struct tcp_skb_cb *scb = TCP_SKB_CB(skb);
3092 u8 sacked = scb->sacked;
3093 u32 acked_pcount;
3094
3095 tcp_ack_tstamp(sk, skb, prior_snd_una);
3096
3097 /* Determine how many packets and what bytes were acked, tso and else */
3098 if (after(scb->end_seq, tp->snd_una)) {
3099 if (tcp_skb_pcount(skb) == 1 ||
3100 !after(tp->snd_una, scb->seq))
3101 break;
3102
3103 acked_pcount = tcp_tso_acked(sk, skb);
3104 if (!acked_pcount)
3105 break;
3106 fully_acked = false;
3107 } else {
3108 /* Speedup tcp_unlink_write_queue() and next loop */
3109 prefetchw(skb->next);
3110 acked_pcount = tcp_skb_pcount(skb);
3111 }
3112
3113 if (unlikely(sacked & TCPCB_RETRANS)) {
3114 if (sacked & TCPCB_SACKED_RETRANS)
3115 tp->retrans_out -= acked_pcount;
3116 flag |= FLAG_RETRANS_DATA_ACKED;
3117 } else if (!(sacked & TCPCB_SACKED_ACKED)) {
3118 last_ackt = skb->skb_mstamp;
3119 WARN_ON_ONCE(last_ackt == 0);
3120 if (!first_ackt)
3121 first_ackt = last_ackt;
3122
3123 last_in_flight = TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->tx.in_flight;
3124 reord = min(pkts_acked, reord);
3125 if (!after(scb->end_seq, tp->high_seq))
3126 flag |= FLAG_ORIG_SACK_ACKED;
3127 }
3128
3129 if (sacked & TCPCB_SACKED_ACKED) {
3130 tp->sacked_out -= acked_pcount;
3131 } else if (tcp_is_sack(tp)) {
3132 tp->delivered += acked_pcount;
3133 if (!tcp_skb_spurious_retrans(tp, skb))
3134 tcp_rack_advance(tp, sacked, scb->end_seq,
3135 skb->skb_mstamp);
3136 }
3137 if (sacked & TCPCB_LOST)
3138 tp->lost_out -= acked_pcount;
3139
3140 tp->packets_out -= acked_pcount;
3141 pkts_acked += acked_pcount;
3142 tcp_rate_skb_delivered(sk, skb, sack->rate);
3143
3144 /* Initial outgoing SYN's get put onto the write_queue
3145 * just like anything else we transmit. It is not
3146 * true data, and if we misinform our callers that
3147 * this ACK acks real data, we will erroneously exit
3148 * connection startup slow start one packet too
3149 * quickly. This is severely frowned upon behavior.
3150 */
3151 if (likely(!(scb->tcp_flags & TCPHDR_SYN))) {
3152 flag |= FLAG_DATA_ACKED;
3153 } else {
3154 flag |= FLAG_SYN_ACKED;
3155 tp->retrans_stamp = 0;
3156 }
3157
3158 if (!fully_acked)
3159 break;
3160
3161 tcp_unlink_write_queue(skb, sk);
3162 sk_wmem_free_skb(sk, skb);
3163 if (unlikely(skb == tp->retransmit_skb_hint))
3164 tp->retransmit_skb_hint = NULL;
3165 if (unlikely(skb == tp->lost_skb_hint))
3166 tp->lost_skb_hint = NULL;
3167 }
3168
3169 if (!skb)
3170 tcp_chrono_stop(sk, TCP_CHRONO_BUSY);
3171
3172 if (likely(between(tp->snd_up, prior_snd_una, tp->snd_una)))
3173 tp->snd_up = tp->snd_una;
3174
3175 if (skb && (TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->sacked & TCPCB_SACKED_ACKED))
3176 flag |= FLAG_SACK_RENEGING;
3177
3178 if (likely(first_ackt) && !(flag & FLAG_RETRANS_DATA_ACKED)) {
3179 seq_rtt_us = tcp_stamp_us_delta(tp->tcp_mstamp, first_ackt);
3180 ca_rtt_us = tcp_stamp_us_delta(tp->tcp_mstamp, last_ackt);
3181 }
3182 if (sack->first_sackt) {
3183 sack_rtt_us = tcp_stamp_us_delta(tp->tcp_mstamp, sack->first_sackt);
3184 ca_rtt_us = tcp_stamp_us_delta(tp->tcp_mstamp, sack->last_sackt);
3185 }
3186 rtt_update = tcp_ack_update_rtt(sk, flag, seq_rtt_us, sack_rtt_us,
3187 ca_rtt_us, sack->rate);
3188
3189 if (flag & FLAG_ACKED) {
3190 flag |= FLAG_SET_XMIT_TIMER; /* set TLP or RTO timer */
3191 if (unlikely(icsk->icsk_mtup.probe_size &&
3192 !after(tp->mtu_probe.probe_seq_end, tp->snd_una))) {
3193 tcp_mtup_probe_success(sk);
3194 }
3195
3196 if (tcp_is_reno(tp)) {
3197 tcp_remove_reno_sacks(sk, pkts_acked);
3198
3199 /* If any of the cumulatively ACKed segments was
3200 * retransmitted, non-SACK case cannot confirm that
3201 * progress was due to original transmission due to
3202 * lack of TCPCB_SACKED_ACKED bits even if some of
3203 * the packets may have been never retransmitted.
3204 */
3205 if (flag & FLAG_RETRANS_DATA_ACKED)
3206 flag &= ~FLAG_ORIG_SACK_ACKED;
3207 } else {
3208 int delta;
3209
3210 /* Non-retransmitted hole got filled? That's reordering */
3211 if (reord < prior_fackets && reord <= tp->fackets_out)
3212 tcp_update_reordering(sk, tp->fackets_out - reord, 0);
3213
3214 delta = tcp_is_fack(tp) ? pkts_acked :
3215 prior_sacked - tp->sacked_out;
3216 tp->lost_cnt_hint -= min(tp->lost_cnt_hint, delta);
3217 }
3218
3219 tp->fackets_out -= min(pkts_acked, tp->fackets_out);
3220
3221 } else if (skb && rtt_update && sack_rtt_us >= 0 &&
3222 sack_rtt_us > tcp_stamp_us_delta(tp->tcp_mstamp, skb->skb_mstamp)) {
3223 /* Do not re-arm RTO if the sack RTT is measured from data sent
3224 * after when the head was last (re)transmitted. Otherwise the
3225 * timeout may continue to extend in loss recovery.
3226 */
3227 flag |= FLAG_SET_XMIT_TIMER; /* set TLP or RTO timer */
3228 }
3229
3230 if (icsk->icsk_ca_ops->pkts_acked) {
3231 struct ack_sample sample = { .pkts_acked = pkts_acked,
3232 .rtt_us = sack->rate->rtt_us,
3233 .in_flight = last_in_flight };
3234
3235 icsk->icsk_ca_ops->pkts_acked(sk, &sample);
3236 }
3237
3238#if FASTRETRANS_DEBUG > 0
3239 WARN_ON((int)tp->sacked_out < 0);
3240 WARN_ON((int)tp->lost_out < 0);
3241 WARN_ON((int)tp->retrans_out < 0);
3242 if (!tp->packets_out && tcp_is_sack(tp)) {
3243 icsk = inet_csk(sk);
3244 if (tp->lost_out) {
3245 pr_debug("Leak l=%u %d\n",
3246 tp->lost_out, icsk->icsk_ca_state);
3247 tp->lost_out = 0;
3248 }
3249 if (tp->sacked_out) {
3250 pr_debug("Leak s=%u %d\n",
3251 tp->sacked_out, icsk->icsk_ca_state);
3252 tp->sacked_out = 0;
3253 }
3254 if (tp->retrans_out) {
3255 pr_debug("Leak r=%u %d\n",
3256 tp->retrans_out, icsk->icsk_ca_state);
3257 tp->retrans_out = 0;
3258 }
3259 }
3260#endif
3261 *acked = pkts_acked;
3262 return flag;
3263}

3265static void tcp_ack_probe(struct sock *sk)
3266{
3267 const struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
3268 struct inet_connection_sock *icsk = inet_csk(sk);
3269
3270 /* Was it a usable window open? */
3271
3272 if (!after(TCP_SKB_CB(tcp_send_head(sk))->end_seq, tcp_wnd_end(tp))) {
3273 icsk->icsk_backoff = 0;
3274 inet_csk_clear_xmit_timer(sk, ICSK_TIME_PROBE0);
3275 /* Socket must be waked up by subsequent tcp_data_snd_check().
3276 * This function is not for random using!
3277 */
3278 } else {
3279 unsigned long when = tcp_probe0_when(sk, TCP_RTO_MAX);
3280
3281 inet_csk_reset_xmit_timer(sk, ICSK_TIME_PROBE0,
3282 when, TCP_RTO_MAX);
3283 }
3284}

3292/* Decide wheather to run the increase function of congestion control. */
3293static inline bool tcp_may_raise_cwnd(const struct sock *sk, const int flag)
3294{
3295 /* If reordering is high then always grow cwnd whenever data is
3296 * delivered regardless of its ordering. Otherwise stay conservative
3297 * and only grow cwnd on in-order delivery (RFC5681). A stretched ACK w/
3298 * new SACK or ECE mark may first advance cwnd here and later reduce
3299 * cwnd in tcp_fastretrans_alert() based on more states.
3300 */
3301 if (tcp_sk(sk)->reordering > sock_net(sk)->ipv4.sysctl_tcp_reordering)
3302 return flag & FLAG_FORWARD_PROGRESS;
3303
3304 return flag & FLAG_DATA_ACKED;
3305}
3306
3307/* The "ultimate" congestion control function that aims to replace the rigid
3308 * cwnd increase and decrease control (tcp_cong_avoid,tcp_*cwnd_reduction).
3309 * It's called toward the end of processing an ACK with precise rate
3310 * information. All transmission or retransmission are delayed afterwards.
3311 */
3312static void tcp_cong_control(struct sock *sk, u32 ack, u32 acked_sacked,
3313 int flag, const struct rate_sample *rs)
3314{
3315 const struct inet_connection_sock *icsk = inet_csk(sk);
3316
3317 if (icsk->icsk_ca_ops->cong_control) {
3318 icsk->icsk_ca_ops->cong_control(sk, rs);
3319 return;
3320 }
3321
3322 if (tcp_in_cwnd_reduction(sk)) {
3323 /* Reduce cwnd if state mandates */
3324 tcp_cwnd_reduction(sk, acked_sacked, flag);
3325 } else if (tcp_may_raise_cwnd(sk, flag)) {
3326 /* Advance cwnd if state allows */
3327 tcp_cong_avoid(sk, ack, acked_sacked);
3328 }
3329 tcp_update_pacing_rate(sk);
3330}

3332/* Check that window update is acceptable.
3333 * The function assumes that snd_una<=ack<=snd_next.
3334 */
3335static inline bool tcp_may_update_window(const struct tcp_sock *tp,
3336 const u32 ack, const u32 ack_seq,
3337 const u32 nwin)
3338{
3339 return after(ack, tp->snd_una) ||
3340 after(ack_seq, tp->snd_wl1) ||
3341 (ack_seq == tp->snd_wl1 && nwin > tp->snd_wnd);
3342}

3344/* If we update tp->snd_una, also update tp->bytes_acked */
3345static void tcp_snd_una_update(struct tcp_sock *tp, u32 ack)
3346{
3347 u32 delta = ack - tp->snd_una;
3348
3349 sock_owned_by_me((struct sock *)tp);
3350 tp->bytes_acked += delta;
3351 tp->snd_una = ack;
3352}
3353
3354/* If we update tp->rcv_nxt, also update tp->bytes_received */
3355static void tcp_rcv_nxt_update(struct tcp_sock *tp, u32 seq)
3356{
3357 u32 delta = seq - tp->rcv_nxt;
3358
3359 sock_owned_by_me((struct sock *)tp);
3360 tp->bytes_received += delta;
3361 tp->rcv_nxt = seq;
3362}
3363
3364/* Update our send window.
3365 *
3366 * Window update algorithm, described in RFC793/RFC1122 (used in linux-2.2
3367 * and in FreeBSD. NetBSD's one is even worse.) is wrong.
3368 */
3369static int tcp_ack_update_window(struct sock *sk, const struct sk_buff *skb, u32 ack,
3370 u32 ack_seq)
3371{
3372 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
3373 int flag = 0;
3374 u32 nwin = ntohs(tcp_hdr(skb)->window);
3375
3376 if (likely(!tcp_hdr(skb)->syn))
3377 nwin <<= tp->rx_opt.snd_wscale;
3378
3379 if (tcp_may_update_window(tp, ack, ack_seq, nwin)) {
3380 flag |= FLAG_WIN_UPDATE;
3381 tcp_update_wl(tp, ack_seq);
3382
3383 if (tp->snd_wnd != nwin) {
3384 tp->snd_wnd = nwin;
3385
3386 /* Note, it is the only place, where
3387 * fast path is recovered for sending TCP.
3388 */
3389 tp->pred_flags = 0;
3390 tcp_fast_path_check(sk);
3391
3392 if (tcp_send_head(sk))
3393 tcp_slow_start_after_idle_check(sk);
3394
3395 if (nwin > tp->max_window) {
3396 tp->max_window = nwin;
3397 tcp_sync_mss(sk, inet_csk(sk)->icsk_pmtu_cookie);
3398 }
3399 }
3400 }
3401
3402 tcp_snd_una_update(tp, ack);
3403
3404 return flag;
3405}
3406
3407static bool __tcp_oow_rate_limited(struct net *net, int mib_idx,
3408 u32 *last_oow_ack_time)
3409{
3410 if (*last_oow_ack_time) {
3411 s32 elapsed = (s32)(tcp_jiffies32 - *last_oow_ack_time);
3412
3413 if (0 <= elapsed && elapsed < sysctl_tcp_invalid_ratelimit) {
3414 NET_INC_STATS(net, mib_idx);
3415 return true; /* rate-limited: don't send yet! */
3416 }
3417 }
3418
3419 *last_oow_ack_time = tcp_jiffies32;
3420
3421 return false; /* not rate-limited: go ahead, send dupack now! */
3422}
3423
3424/* Return true if we're currently rate-limiting out-of-window ACKs and
3425 * thus shouldn't send a dupack right now. We rate-limit dupacks in
3426 * response to out-of-window SYNs or ACKs to mitigate ACK loops or DoS
3427 * attacks that send repeated SYNs or ACKs for the same connection. To
3428 * do this, we do not send a duplicate SYNACK or ACK if the remote
3429 * endpoint is sending out-of-window SYNs or pure ACKs at a high rate.
3430 */
3431bool tcp_oow_rate_limited(struct net *net, const struct sk_buff *skb,
3432 int mib_idx, u32 *last_oow_ack_time)
3433{
3434 /* Data packets without SYNs are not likely part of an ACK loop. */
3435 if ((TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->seq != TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->end_seq) &&
3436 !tcp_hdr(skb)->syn)
3437 return false;
3438
3439 return __tcp_oow_rate_limited(net, mib_idx, last_oow_ack_time);
3440}
3441
3442/* RFC 5961 7 [ACK Throttling] */
3443static void tcp_send_challenge_ack(struct sock *sk, const struct sk_buff *skb)
3444{
3445 /* unprotected vars, we dont care of overwrites */
3446 static u32 challenge_timestamp;
3447 static unsigned int challenge_count;
3448 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
3449 u32 count, now;
3450
3451 /* First check our per-socket dupack rate limit. */
3452 if (__tcp_oow_rate_limited(sock_net(sk),
3453 LINUX_MIB_TCPACKSKIPPEDCHALLENGE,
3454 &tp->last_oow_ack_time))
3455 return;
3456
3457 /* Then check host-wide RFC 5961 rate limit. */
3458 now = jiffies / HZ;
3459 if (now != challenge_timestamp) {
3460 u32 half = (sysctl_tcp_challenge_ack_limit + 1) >> 1;
3461
3462 challenge_timestamp = now;
3463 WRITE_ONCE(challenge_count, half +
3464 prandom_u32_max(sysctl_tcp_challenge_ack_limit));
3465 }
3466 count = READ_ONCE(challenge_count);
3467 if (count > 0) {
3468 WRITE_ONCE(challenge_count, count - 1);
3469 NET_INC_STATS(sock_net(sk), LINUX_MIB_TCPCHALLENGEACK);
3470 tcp_send_ack(sk);
3471 }
3472}

3476 tp->rx_opt.ts_recent = tp->rx_opt.rcv_tsval;
3477 tp->rx_opt.ts_recent_stamp = get_seconds();

3480static void tcp_replace_ts_recent(struct tcp_sock *tp, u32 seq)
3481{
3482 if (tp->rx_opt.saw_tstamp && !after(seq, tp->rcv_wup)) {
3483 /* PAWS bug workaround wrt. ACK frames, the PAWS discard
3484 * extra check below makes sure this can only happen
3485 * for pure ACK frames. -DaveM
3486 *
3487 * Not only, also it occurs for expired timestamps.
3488 */
3489

3494
3495/* This routine deals with acks during a TLP episode.
3496 * We mark the end of a TLP episode on receiving TLP dupack or when
3497 * ack is after tlp_high_seq.
3498 * Ref: loss detection algorithm in draft-dukkipati-tcpm-tcp-loss-probe.
3499 */
3500static void tcp_process_tlp_ack(struct sock *sk, u32 ack, int flag)
3501{
3502 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
3503
3504 if (before(ack, tp->tlp_high_seq))
3505 return;
3506
3507 if (flag & FLAG_DSACKING_ACK) {
3508 /* This DSACK means original and TLP probe arrived; no loss */
3509 tp->tlp_high_seq = 0;
3510 } else if (after(ack, tp->tlp_high_seq)) {
3511 /* ACK advances: there was a loss, so reduce cwnd. Reset
3512 * tlp_high_seq in tcp_init_cwnd_reduction()
3513 */
3514 tcp_init_cwnd_reduction(sk);
3515 tcp_set_ca_state(sk, TCP_CA_CWR);
3516 tcp_end_cwnd_reduction(sk);
3517 tcp_try_keep_open(sk);
3518 NET_INC_STATS(sock_net(sk),
3519 LINUX_MIB_TCPLOSSPROBERECOVERY);
3520 } else if (!(flag & (FLAG_SND_UNA_ADVANCED |
3521 FLAG_NOT_DUP | FLAG_DATA_SACKED))) {
3522 /* Pure dupack: original and TLP probe arrived; no loss */
3523 tp->tlp_high_seq = 0;
3524 }
3525}
3526
3527static inline void tcp_in_ack_event(struct sock *sk, u32 flags)
3528{
3529 const struct inet_connection_sock *icsk = inet_csk(sk);
3530
3531 if (icsk->icsk_ca_ops->in_ack_event)
3532 icsk->icsk_ca_ops->in_ack_event(sk, flags);
3533}
3534
3535/* Congestion control has updated the cwnd already. So if we're in
3536 * loss recovery then now we do any new sends (for FRTO) or
3537 * retransmits (for CA_Loss or CA_recovery) that make sense.
3538 */
3539static void tcp_xmit_recovery(struct sock *sk, int rexmit)
3540{
3541 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
3542
3543 if (rexmit == REXMIT_NONE)
3544 return;
3545
3546 if (unlikely(rexmit == 2)) {
3547 __tcp_push_pending_frames(sk, tcp_current_mss(sk),
3548 TCP_NAGLE_OFF);
3549 if (after(tp->snd_nxt, tp->high_seq))
3550 return;
3551 tp->frto = 0;
3552 }
3553 tcp_xmit_retransmit_queue(sk);
3554}
3555
3556/* This routine deals with incoming acks, but not outgoing ones. */
3557static int tcp_ack(struct sock *sk, const struct sk_buff *skb, int flag)
3558{
3559 struct inet_connection_sock *icsk = inet_csk(sk);
3560 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
3561 struct tcp_sacktag_state sack_state;
3562 struct rate_sample rs = { .prior_delivered = 0 };
3563 u32 prior_snd_una = tp->snd_una;
3564 bool is_sack_reneg = tp->is_sack_reneg;
3565 u32 ack_seq = TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->seq;
3566 u32 ack = TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->ack_seq;
3567 bool is_dupack = false;
3568 u32 prior_fackets;
3569 int prior_packets = tp->packets_out;
3570 u32 delivered = tp->delivered;
3571 u32 lost = tp->lost;
3572 int acked = 0; /* Number of packets newly acked */
3573 int rexmit = REXMIT_NONE; /* Flag to (re)transmit to recover losses */
3574
3575 sack_state.first_sackt = 0;
3576 sack_state.rate = &rs;
3577
3578 /* We very likely will need to access write queue head. */
3579 prefetchw(sk->sk_write_queue.next);
3580
3581 /* If the ack is older than previous acks
3582 * then we can probably ignore it.
3583 */
3584 if (before(ack, prior_snd_una)) {
3585 /* RFC 5961 5.2 [Blind Data Injection Attack].[Mitigation] */
3586 if (before(ack, prior_snd_una - tp->max_window)) {
3587 if (!(flag & FLAG_NO_CHALLENGE_ACK))
3588 tcp_send_challenge_ack(sk, skb);
3589 return -1;
3590 }
3591 goto old_ack;
3592 }
3593
3594 /* If the ack includes data we haven't sent yet, discard
3595 * this segment (RFC793 Section 3.9).
3596 */
3597 if (after(ack, tp->snd_nxt))
3598 goto invalid_ack;
3599
3600 if (after(ack, prior_snd_una)) {
3601 flag |= FLAG_SND_UNA_ADVANCED;
3602 icsk->icsk_retransmits = 0;
3603 }
3604
3605 prior_fackets = tp->fackets_out;
3606 rs.prior_in_flight = tcp_packets_in_flight(tp);
3607
3608 /* ts_recent update must be made after we are sure that the packet
3609 * is in window.
3610 */
3611 if (flag & FLAG_UPDATE_TS_RECENT)
3612 tcp_replace_ts_recent(tp, TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->seq);
3613
3614 if (!(flag & FLAG_SLOWPATH) && after(ack, prior_snd_una)) {
3615 /* Window is constant, pure forward advance.
3616 * No more checks are required.
3617 * Note, we use the fact that SND.UNA>=SND.WL2.
3618 */
3619 tcp_update_wl(tp, ack_seq);
3620 tcp_snd_una_update(tp, ack);
3621 flag |= FLAG_WIN_UPDATE;
3622
3623 tcp_in_ack_event(sk, CA_ACK_WIN_UPDATE);
3624
3625 NET_INC_STATS(sock_net(sk), LINUX_MIB_TCPHPACKS);
3626 } else {
3627 u32 ack_ev_flags = CA_ACK_SLOWPATH;
3628
3629 if (ack_seq != TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->end_seq)
3630 flag |= FLAG_DATA;
3631 else
3632 NET_INC_STATS(sock_net(sk), LINUX_MIB_TCPPUREACKS);
3633
3634 flag |= tcp_ack_update_window(sk, skb, ack, ack_seq);
3635
3636 if (TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->sacked)
3637 flag |= tcp_sacktag_write_queue(sk, skb, prior_snd_una,
3638 &sack_state);
3639
3640 if (tcp_ecn_rcv_ecn_echo(tp, tcp_hdr(skb))) {
3641 flag |= FLAG_ECE;
3642 ack_ev_flags |= CA_ACK_ECE;
3643 }
3644
3645 if (flag & FLAG_WIN_UPDATE)
3646 ack_ev_flags |= CA_ACK_WIN_UPDATE;
3647
3648 tcp_in_ack_event(sk, ack_ev_flags);
3649 }
3650
3651 /* We passed data and got it acked, remove any soft error
3652 * log. Something worked...
3653 */
3654 sk->sk_err_soft = 0;
3655 icsk->icsk_probes_out = 0;
3656 tp->rcv_tstamp = tcp_jiffies32;
3657 if (!prior_packets)
3658 goto no_queue;
3659
3660 /* See if we can take anything off of the retransmit queue. */
3661 flag |= tcp_clean_rtx_queue(sk, prior_fackets, prior_snd_una, &acked,
3662 &sack_state);
3663
3664 if (tp->tlp_high_seq)
3665 tcp_process_tlp_ack(sk, ack, flag);
3666 /* If needed, reset TLP/RTO timer; RACK may later override this. */
3667 if (flag & FLAG_SET_XMIT_TIMER)
3668 tcp_set_xmit_timer(sk);
3669
3670 if (tcp_ack_is_dubious(sk, flag)) {
3671 is_dupack = !(flag & (FLAG_SND_UNA_ADVANCED | FLAG_NOT_DUP));
3672 tcp_fastretrans_alert(sk, acked, is_dupack, &flag, &rexmit);
3673 }
3674
3675 if ((flag & FLAG_FORWARD_PROGRESS) || !(flag & FLAG_NOT_DUP))
3676 sk_dst_confirm(sk);
3677
3678 delivered = tp->delivered - delivered; /* freshly ACKed or SACKed */
3679 lost = tp->lost - lost; /* freshly marked lost */
3680 tcp_rate_gen(sk, delivered, lost, is_sack_reneg, sack_state.rate);
3681 tcp_cong_control(sk, ack, delivered, flag, sack_state.rate);
3682 tcp_xmit_recovery(sk, rexmit);
3683 return 1;
3684
3685no_queue:
3686 /* If data was DSACKed, see if we can undo a cwnd reduction. */
3687 if (flag & FLAG_DSACKING_ACK)
3688 tcp_fastretrans_alert(sk, acked, is_dupack, &flag, &rexmit);
3689 /* If this ack opens up a zero window, clear backoff. It was
3690 * being used to time the probes, and is probably far higher than
3691 * it needs to be for normal retransmission.
3692 */
3693 if (tcp_send_head(sk))
3694 tcp_ack_probe(sk);
3695
3696 if (tp->tlp_high_seq)
3697 tcp_process_tlp_ack(sk, ack, flag);
3698 return 1;
3699
3700invalid_ack:
3701 SOCK_DEBUG(sk, "Ack %u after %u:%u\n", ack, tp->snd_una, tp->snd_nxt);
3702 return -1;
3703
3704old_ack:
3705 /* If data was SACKed, tag it and see if we should send more data.
3706 * If data was DSACKed, see if we can undo a cwnd reduction.
3707 */
3708 if (TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->sacked) {
3709 flag |= tcp_sacktag_write_queue(sk, skb, prior_snd_una,
3710 &sack_state);
3711 tcp_fastretrans_alert(sk, acked, is_dupack, &flag, &rexmit);
3712 tcp_xmit_recovery(sk, rexmit);
3713 }
3714
3715 SOCK_DEBUG(sk, "Ack %u before %u:%u\n", ack, tp->snd_una, tp->snd_nxt);
3716 return 0;
3717}
3718
3719static void tcp_parse_fastopen_option(int len, const unsigned char *cookie,
3720 bool syn, struct tcp_fastopen_cookie *foc,
3721 bool exp_opt)
3722{
3723 /* Valid only in SYN or SYN-ACK with an even length. */
3724 if (!foc || !syn || len < 0 || (len & 1))
3725 return;
3726
3727 if (len >= TCP_FASTOPEN_COOKIE_MIN &&
3728 len <= TCP_FASTOPEN_COOKIE_MAX)
3729 memcpy(foc->val, cookie, len);
3730 else if (len != 0)
3731 len = -1;
3732 foc->len = len;
3733 foc->exp = exp_opt;
3734}
3735
3736/* Look for tcp options. Normally only called on SYN and SYNACK packets.
3737 * But, this can also be called on packets in the established flow when
3738 * the fast version below fails.
3739 */
3740void tcp_parse_options(const struct net *net,
3741 const struct sk_buff *skb,
3742 struct tcp_options_received *opt_rx, int estab,
3743 struct tcp_fastopen_cookie *foc)
3744{
3745 const unsigned char *ptr;
3746 const struct tcphdr *th = tcp_hdr(skb);
3747 int length = (th->doff * 4) - sizeof(struct tcphdr);
3748
3749 ptr = (const unsigned char *)(th + 1);
3750 opt_rx->saw_tstamp = 0;
3751
3752 while (length > 0) {
3753 int opcode = *ptr++;
3754 int opsize;
3755
3756 switch (opcode) {
3757 case TCPOPT_EOL:
3758 return;
3759 case TCPOPT_NOP: /* Ref: RFC 793 section 3.1 */
3760 length--;
3761 continue;
3762 default:
3763 opsize = *ptr++;
3764 if (opsize < 2) /* "silly options" */
3765 return;
3766 if (opsize > length)
3767 return; /* don't parse partial options */
3768 switch (opcode) {
3769 case TCPOPT_MSS:
3770 if (opsize == TCPOLEN_MSS && th->syn && !estab) {
3771 u16 in_mss = get_unaligned_be16(ptr);
3772 if (in_mss) {
3773 if (opt_rx->user_mss &&
3774 opt_rx->user_mss < in_mss)
3775 in_mss = opt_rx->user_mss;
3776 opt_rx->mss_clamp = in_mss;
3777 }
3778 }
3779 break;
3780 case TCPOPT_WINDOW:
3781 if (opsize == TCPOLEN_WINDOW && th->syn &&
3782 !estab && net->ipv4.sysctl_tcp_window_scaling) {
3783 __u8 snd_wscale = *(__u8 *)ptr;
3784 opt_rx->wscale_ok = 1;
3785 if (snd_wscale > TCP_MAX_WSCALE) {
3786 net_info_ratelimited("%s: Illegal window scaling value %d > %u received\n",
3787 __func__,
3788 snd_wscale,
3789 TCP_MAX_WSCALE);
3790 snd_wscale = TCP_MAX_WSCALE;
3791 }
3792 opt_rx->snd_wscale = snd_wscale;
3793 }
3794 break;
3795 case TCPOPT_TIMESTAMP:
3796 if ((opsize == TCPOLEN_TIMESTAMP) &&
3797 ((estab && opt_rx->tstamp_ok) ||
3798 (!estab && net->ipv4.sysctl_tcp_timestamps))) {
3799 opt_rx->saw_tstamp = 1;
3800 opt_rx->rcv_tsval = get_unaligned_be32(ptr);
3801 opt_rx->rcv_tsecr = get_unaligned_be32(ptr + 4);
3802 }
3803 break;
3804 case TCPOPT_SACK_PERM:
3805 if (opsize == TCPOLEN_SACK_PERM && th->syn &&
3806 !estab && net->ipv4.sysctl_tcp_sack) {
3807 opt_rx->sack_ok = TCP_SACK_SEEN;
3808 tcp_sack_reset(opt_rx);
3809 }
3810 break;
3811
3812 case TCPOPT_SACK:
3813 if ((opsize >= (TCPOLEN_SACK_BASE + TCPOLEN_SACK_PERBLOCK)) &&
3814 !((opsize - TCPOLEN_SACK_BASE) % TCPOLEN_SACK_PERBLOCK) &&
3815 opt_rx->sack_ok) {
3816 TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->sacked = (ptr - 2) - (unsigned char *)th;
3817 }
3818 break;
3819#ifdef CONFIG_TCP_MD5SIG
3820 case TCPOPT_MD5SIG:
3821 /*
3822 * The MD5 Hash has already been
3823 * checked (see tcp_v{4,6}_do_rcv()).
3824 */
3825 break;
3826#endif
3827 case TCPOPT_FASTOPEN:
3828 tcp_parse_fastopen_option(
3829 opsize - TCPOLEN_FASTOPEN_BASE,
3830 ptr, th->syn, foc, false);
3831 break;
3832
3833 case TCPOPT_EXP:
3834 /* Fast Open option shares code 254 using a
3835 * 16 bits magic number.
3836 */
3837 if (opsize >= TCPOLEN_EXP_FASTOPEN_BASE &&
3838 get_unaligned_be16(ptr) ==
3839 TCPOPT_FASTOPEN_MAGIC)
3840 tcp_parse_fastopen_option(opsize -
3841 TCPOLEN_EXP_FASTOPEN_BASE,
3842 ptr + 2, th->syn, foc, true);
3843 break;
3844
3845 }
3846 ptr += opsize-2;
3847 length -= opsize;
3848 }
3849 }
3850}
3851EXPORT_SYMBOL(tcp_parse_options);
3852
3853static bool tcp_parse_aligned_timestamp(struct tcp_sock *tp, const struct tcphdr *th)
3854{
3855 const __be32 *ptr = (const __be32 *)(th + 1);
3856
3857 if (*ptr == htonl((TCPOPT_NOP << 24) | (TCPOPT_NOP << 16)
3858 | (TCPOPT_TIMESTAMP << 8) | TCPOLEN_TIMESTAMP)) {
3859 tp->rx_opt.saw_tstamp = 1;
3860 ++ptr;
3861 tp->rx_opt.rcv_tsval = ntohl(*ptr);
3862 ++ptr;
3863 if (*ptr)
3864 tp->rx_opt.rcv_tsecr = ntohl(*ptr) - tp->tsoffset;
3865 else
3866 tp->rx_opt.rcv_tsecr = 0;
3867 return true;
3868 }
3869 return false;
3870}
3871
3872/* Fast parse options. This hopes to only see timestamps.
3873 * If it is wrong it falls back on tcp_parse_options().
3874 */
3875static bool tcp_fast_parse_options(const struct net *net,
3876 const struct sk_buff *skb,
3877 const struct tcphdr *th, struct tcp_sock *tp)
3878{
3879 /* In the spirit of fast parsing, compare doff directly to constant
3880 * values. Because equality is used, short doff can be ignored here.
3881 */
3882 if (th->doff == (sizeof(*th) / 4)) {
3883 tp->rx_opt.saw_tstamp = 0;
3884 return false;
3885 } else if (tp->rx_opt.tstamp_ok &&
3886 th->doff == ((sizeof(*th) + TCPOLEN_TSTAMP_ALIGNED) / 4)) {
3887 if (tcp_parse_aligned_timestamp(tp, th))
3888 return true;
3889 }
3890
3891 tcp_parse_options(net, skb, &tp->rx_opt, 1, NULL);
3892 if (tp->rx_opt.saw_tstamp && tp->rx_opt.rcv_tsecr)
3893 tp->rx_opt.rcv_tsecr -= tp->tsoffset;
3894
3895 return true;
3896}

3898#ifdef CONFIG_TCP_MD5SIG
3899/*
3900 * Parse MD5 Signature option
3901 */
3902const u8 *tcp_parse_md5sig_option(const struct tcphdr *th)
3903{
3904 int length = (th->doff << 2) - sizeof(*th);
3905 const u8 *ptr = (const u8 *)(th + 1);
3906
3907 /* If not enough data remaining, we can short cut */
3908 while (length >= TCPOLEN_MD5SIG) {
3909 int opcode = *ptr++;
3910 int opsize;
3911
3912 switch (opcode) {
3913 case TCPOPT_EOL:
3914 return NULL;
3915 case TCPOPT_NOP:
3916 length--;
3917 continue;
3918 default:
3919 opsize = *ptr++;
3920 if (opsize < 2 || opsize > length)
3921 return NULL;
3922 if (opcode == TCPOPT_MD5SIG)
3923 return opsize == TCPOLEN_MD5SIG ? ptr : NULL;
3924 }
3925 ptr += opsize - 2;
3926 length -= opsize;
3927 }
3928 return NULL;
3929}
3930EXPORT_SYMBOL(tcp_parse_md5sig_option);
3931#endif
3932
3933/* Sorry, PAWS as specified is broken wrt. pure-ACKs -DaveM
3934 *
3935 * It is not fatal. If this ACK does _not_ change critical state (seqs, window)
3936 * it can pass through stack. So, the following predicate verifies that
3937 * this segment is not used for anything but congestion avoidance or
3938 * fast retransmit. Moreover, we even are able to eliminate most of such
3939 * second order effects, if we apply some small "replay" window (~RTO)
3940 * to timestamp space.
3941 *
3942 * All these measures still do not guarantee that we reject wrapped ACKs
3943 * on networks with high bandwidth, when sequence space is recycled fastly,
3944 * but it guarantees that such events will be very rare and do not affect
3945 * connection seriously. This doesn't look nice, but alas, PAWS is really
3946 * buggy extension.
3947 *
3948 * [ Later note. Even worse! It is buggy for segments _with_ data. RFC
3949 * states that events when retransmit arrives after original data are rare.
3950 * It is a blatant lie. VJ forgot about fast retransmit! 8)8) It is
3951 * the biggest problem on large power networks even with minor reordering.
3952 * OK, let's give it small replay window. If peer clock is even 1hz, it is safe
3953 * up to bandwidth of 18Gigabit/sec. 8) ]
3954 */
3955
3956static int tcp_disordered_ack(const struct sock *sk, const struct sk_buff *skb)
3957{
3958 const struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
3959 const struct tcphdr *th = tcp_hdr(skb);
3960 u32 seq = TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->seq;
3961 u32 ack = TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->ack_seq;
3962
3963 return (/* 1. Pure ACK with correct sequence number. */
3964 (th->ack && seq == TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->end_seq && seq == tp->rcv_nxt) &&
3965
3966 /* 2. ... and duplicate ACK. */
3967 ack == tp->snd_una &&
3968
3969 /* 3. ... and does not update window. */
3970 !tcp_may_update_window(tp, ack, seq, ntohs(th->window) << tp->rx_opt.snd_wscale) &&
3971
3972 /* 4. ... and sits in replay window. */
3973 (s32)(tp->rx_opt.ts_recent - tp->rx_opt.rcv_tsval) <= (inet_csk(sk)->icsk_rto * 1024) / HZ);
3974}
3975
3976static inline bool tcp_paws_discard(const struct sock *sk,
3977 const struct sk_buff *skb)
3978{
3979 const struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
3980
3981 return !tcp_paws_check(&tp->rx_opt, TCP_PAWS_WINDOW) &&
3982 !tcp_disordered_ack(sk, skb);
3983}
3984
3985/* Check segment sequence number for validity.
3986 *
3987 * Segment controls are considered valid, if the segment
3988 * fits to the window after truncation to the window. Acceptability
3989 * of data (and SYN, FIN, of course) is checked separately.
3990 * See tcp_data_queue(), for example.
3991 *
3992 * Also, controls (RST is main one) are accepted using RCV.WUP instead
3993 * of RCV.NXT. Peer still did not advance his SND.UNA when we
3994 * delayed ACK, so that hisSND.UNA<=ourRCV.WUP.
3995 * (borrowed from freebsd)
3996 */
3997
3998static inline bool tcp_sequence(const struct tcp_sock *tp, u32 seq, u32 end_seq)
3999{
4000 return !before(end_seq, tp->rcv_wup) &&
4001 !after(seq, tp->rcv_nxt + tcp_receive_window(tp));
4002}
4003
4004/* When we get a reset we do this. */
4005void tcp_reset(struct sock *sk)
4006{
4007 /* We want the right error as BSD sees it (and indeed as we do). */
4008 switch (sk->sk_state) {
4009 case TCP_SYN_SENT:
4010 sk->sk_err = ECONNREFUSED;
4011 break;
4012 case TCP_CLOSE_WAIT:
4013 sk->sk_err = EPIPE;
4014 break;
4015 case TCP_CLOSE:
4016 return;
4017 default:
4018 sk->sk_err = ECONNRESET;
4019 }
4020 /* This barrier is coupled with smp_rmb() in tcp_poll() */
4021 smp_wmb();
4022
4023 tcp_write_queue_purge(sk);
4024 tcp_done(sk);
4025
4026 if (!sock_flag(sk, SOCK_DEAD))
4027 sk->sk_error_report(sk);
4028}
4029
4030/*
4031 * Process the FIN bit. This now behaves as it is supposed to work
4032 * and the FIN takes effect when it is validly part of sequence
4033 * space. Not before when we get holes.
4034 *
4035 * If we are ESTABLISHED, a received fin moves us to CLOSE-WAIT
4036 * (and thence onto LAST-ACK and finally, CLOSE, we never enter
4037 * TIME-WAIT)
4038 *
4039 * If we are in FINWAIT-1, a received FIN indicates simultaneous
4040 * close and we go into CLOSING (and later onto TIME-WAIT)
4041 *
4042 * If we are in FINWAIT-2, a received FIN moves us to TIME-WAIT.
4043 */
4044void tcp_fin(struct sock *sk)
4045{
4046 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
4047
4048 inet_csk_schedule_ack(sk);
4049
4050 sk->sk_shutdown |= RCV_SHUTDOWN;
4051 sock_set_flag(sk, SOCK_DONE);
4052
4053 switch (sk->sk_state) {
4054 case TCP_SYN_RECV:
4055 case TCP_ESTABLISHED:
4056 /* Move to CLOSE_WAIT */
4057 tcp_set_state(sk, TCP_CLOSE_WAIT);
4058 inet_csk(sk)->icsk_ack.pingpong = 1;
4059 break;
4060
4061 case TCP_CLOSE_WAIT:
4062 case TCP_CLOSING:
4063 /* Received a retransmission of the FIN, do
4064 * nothing.
4065 */
4066 break;
4067 case TCP_LAST_ACK:
4068 /* RFC793: Remain in the LAST-ACK state. */
4069 break;
4070
4071 case TCP_FIN_WAIT1:
4072 /* This case occurs when a simultaneous close
4073 * happens, we must ack the received FIN and
4074 * enter the CLOSING state.
4075 */
4076 tcp_send_ack(sk);
4077 tcp_set_state(sk, TCP_CLOSING);
4078 break;
4079 case TCP_FIN_WAIT2:
4080 /* Received a FIN -- send ACK and enter TIME_WAIT. */
4081 tcp_send_ack(sk);
4082 tcp_time_wait(sk, TCP_TIME_WAIT, 0);
4083 break;
4084 default:
4085 /* Only TCP_LISTEN and TCP_CLOSE are left, in these
4086 * cases we should never reach this piece of code.
4087 */
4088 pr_err("%s: Impossible, sk->sk_state=%d\n",
4089 __func__, sk->sk_state);
4090 break;
4091 }
4092
4093 /* It _is_ possible, that we have something out-of-order _after_ FIN.
4094 * Probably, we should reset in this case. For now drop them.
4095 */
4096 skb_rbtree_purge(&tp->out_of_order_queue);
4097 if (tcp_is_sack(tp))
4098 tcp_sack_reset(&tp->rx_opt);
4099 sk_mem_reclaim(sk);
4100
4101 if (!sock_flag(sk, SOCK_DEAD)) {
4102 sk->sk_state_change(sk);
4103
4104 /* Do not send POLL_HUP for half duplex close. */
4105 if (sk->sk_shutdown == SHUTDOWN_MASK ||
4106 sk->sk_state == TCP_CLOSE)
4107 sk_wake_async(sk, SOCK_WAKE_WAITD, POLL_HUP);
4108 else
4109 sk_wake_async(sk, SOCK_WAKE_WAITD, POLL_IN);
4110 }
4111}
4112
4113static inline bool tcp_sack_extend(struct tcp_sack_block *sp, u32 seq,
4114 u32 end_seq)
4115{
4116 if (!after(seq, sp->end_seq) && !after(sp->start_seq, end_seq)) {
4117 if (before(seq, sp->start_seq))
4118 sp->start_seq = seq;
4119 if (after(end_seq, sp->end_seq))
4120 sp->end_seq = end_seq;
4121 return true;
4122 }
4123 return false;
4124}
4125
4126static void tcp_dsack_set(struct sock *sk, u32 seq, u32 end_seq)
4127{
4128 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
4129
4130 if (tcp_is_sack(tp) && sysctl_tcp_dsack) {
4131 int mib_idx;
4132
4133 if (before(seq, tp->rcv_nxt))
4134 mib_idx = LINUX_MIB_TCPDSACKOLDSENT;
4135 else
4136 mib_idx = LINUX_MIB_TCPDSACKOFOSENT;
4137
4138 NET_INC_STATS(sock_net(sk), mib_idx);
4139
4140 tp->rx_opt.dsack = 1;
4141 tp->duplicate_sack[0].start_seq = seq;
4142 tp->duplicate_sack[0].end_seq = end_seq;
4143 }
4144}
4145
4146static void tcp_dsack_extend(struct sock *sk, u32 seq, u32 end_seq)
4147{
4148 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
4149
4150 if (!tp->rx_opt.dsack)
4151 tcp_dsack_set(sk, seq, end_seq);
4152 else
4153 tcp_sack_extend(tp->duplicate_sack, seq, end_seq);
4154}
4155
4156static void tcp_send_dupack(struct sock *sk, const struct sk_buff *skb)
4157{
4158 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
4159
4160 if (TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->end_seq != TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->seq &&
4161 before(TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->seq, tp->rcv_nxt)) {
4162 NET_INC_STATS(sock_net(sk), LINUX_MIB_DELAYEDACKLOST);
4163 tcp_enter_quickack_mode(sk);
4164
4165 if (tcp_is_sack(tp) && sysctl_tcp_dsack) {
4166 u32 end_seq = TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->end_seq;
4167
4168 if (after(TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->end_seq, tp->rcv_nxt))
4169 end_seq = tp->rcv_nxt;
4170 tcp_dsack_set(sk, TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->seq, end_seq);
4171 }
4172 }
4173
4174 tcp_send_ack(sk);
4175}
4176
4177/* These routines update the SACK block as out-of-order packets arrive or
4178 * in-order packets close up the sequence space.
4179 */
4180static void tcp_sack_maybe_coalesce(struct tcp_sock *tp)
4181{
4182 int this_sack;
4183 struct tcp_sack_block *sp = &tp->selective_acks[0];
4184 struct tcp_sack_block *swalk = sp + 1;
4185
4186 /* See if the recent change to the first SACK eats into
4187 * or hits the sequence space of other SACK blocks, if so coalesce.
4188 */
4189 for (this_sack = 1; this_sack < tp->rx_opt.num_sacks;) {
4190 if (tcp_sack_extend(sp, swalk->start_seq, swalk->end_seq)) {
4191 int i;
4192
4193 /* Zap SWALK, by moving every further SACK up by one slot.
4194 * Decrease num_sacks.
4195 */
4196 tp->rx_opt.num_sacks--;
4197 for (i = this_sack; i < tp->rx_opt.num_sacks; i++)
4198 sp[i] = sp[i + 1];
4199 continue;
4200 }
4201 this_sack++, swalk++;
4202 }
4203}
4204
4205static void tcp_sack_new_ofo_skb(struct sock *sk, u32 seq, u32 end_seq)
4206{
4207 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
4208 struct tcp_sack_block *sp = &tp->selective_acks[0];
4209 int cur_sacks = tp->rx_opt.num_sacks;
4210 int this_sack;
4211
4212 if (!cur_sacks)
4213 goto new_sack;
4214
4215 for (this_sack = 0; this_sack < cur_sacks; this_sack++, sp++) {
4216 if (tcp_sack_extend(sp, seq, end_seq)) {
4217 /* Rotate this_sack to the first one. */
4218 for (; this_sack > 0; this_sack--, sp--)
4219 swap(*sp, *(sp - 1));
4220 if (cur_sacks > 1)
4221 tcp_sack_maybe_coalesce(tp);
4222 return;
4223 }
4224 }
4225
4226 /* Could not find an adjacent existing SACK, build a new one,
4227 * put it at the front, and shift everyone else down. We
4228 * always know there is at least one SACK present already here.
4229 *
4230 * If the sack array is full, forget about the last one.
4231 */
4232 if (this_sack >= TCP_NUM_SACKS) {
4233 this_sack--;
4234 tp->rx_opt.num_sacks--;
4235 sp--;
4236 }
4237 for (; this_sack > 0; this_sack--, sp--)
4238 *sp = *(sp - 1);
4239
4240new_sack:
4241 /* Build the new head SACK, and we're done. */
4242 sp->start_seq = seq;
4243 sp->end_seq = end_seq;
4244 tp->rx_opt.num_sacks++;
4245}
4246
4247/* RCV.NXT advances, some SACKs should be eaten. */
4248
4249static void tcp_sack_remove(struct tcp_sock *tp)
4250{
4251 struct tcp_sack_block *sp = &tp->selective_acks[0];
4252 int num_sacks = tp->rx_opt.num_sacks;
4253 int this_sack;
4254
4255 /* Empty ofo queue, hence, all the SACKs are eaten. Clear. */
4256 if (RB_EMPTY_ROOT(&tp->out_of_order_queue)) {
4257 tp->rx_opt.num_sacks = 0;
4258 return;
4259 }
4260
4261 for (this_sack = 0; this_sack < num_sacks;) {
4262 /* Check if the start of the sack is covered by RCV.NXT. */
4263 if (!before(tp->rcv_nxt, sp->start_seq)) {
4264 int i;
4265
4266 /* RCV.NXT must cover all the block! */
4267 WARN_ON(before(tp->rcv_nxt, sp->end_seq));
4268
4269 /* Zap this SACK, by moving forward any other SACKS. */
4270 for (i = this_sack+1; i < num_sacks; i++)
4271 tp->selective_acks[i-1] = tp->selective_acks[i];
4272 num_sacks--;
4273 continue;
4274 }
4275 this_sack++;
4276 sp++;
4277 }
4278 tp->rx_opt.num_sacks = num_sacks;
4279}

4281enum tcp_queue {
4282 OOO_QUEUE,
4283 RCV_QUEUE,
4284};

4286/**
4287 * tcp_try_coalesce - try to merge skb to prior one
4288 * @sk: socket
4289 * @dest: destination queue
4290 * @to: prior buffer
4291 * @from: buffer to add in queue
4292 * @fragstolen: pointer to boolean
4293 *
4294 * Before queueing skb @from after @to, try to merge them
4295 * to reduce overall memory use and queue lengths, if cost is small.
4296 * Packets in ofo or receive queues can stay a long time.
4297 * Better try to coalesce them right now to avoid future collapses.
4298 * Returns true if caller should free @from instead of queueing it
4299 */
4300static bool tcp_try_coalesce(struct sock *sk,
4301 enum tcp_queue dest,
4302 struct sk_buff *to,
4303 struct sk_buff *from,
4304 bool *fragstolen)
4305{
4306 int delta;
4307
4308 *fragstolen = false;
4309
4310 /* Its possible this segment overlaps with prior segment in queue */
4311 if (TCP_SKB_CB(from)->seq != TCP_SKB_CB(to)->end_seq)
4312 return false;
4313
4314 if (!skb_try_coalesce(to, from, fragstolen, &delta))
4315 return false;
4316
4317 atomic_add(delta, &sk->sk_rmem_alloc);
4318 sk_mem_charge(sk, delta);
4319 NET_INC_STATS(sock_net(sk), LINUX_MIB_TCPRCVCOALESCE);
4320 TCP_SKB_CB(to)->end_seq = TCP_SKB_CB(from)->end_seq;
4321 TCP_SKB_CB(to)->ack_seq = TCP_SKB_CB(from)->ack_seq;
4322 TCP_SKB_CB(to)->tcp_flags |= TCP_SKB_CB(from)->tcp_flags;
4323
4324 if (TCP_SKB_CB(from)->has_rxtstamp) {
4325 TCP_SKB_CB(to)->has_rxtstamp = true;
4326 if (dest == OOO_QUEUE)
4327 TCP_SKB_CB(to)->swtstamp = TCP_SKB_CB(from)->swtstamp;
4328 else
4329 to->tstamp = from->tstamp;
4330 }
4331
4332 return true;
4333}
4334
4335static bool tcp_ooo_try_coalesce(struct sock *sk,
4336 struct sk_buff *to,
4337 struct sk_buff *from,
4338 bool *fragstolen)
4339{
4340 bool res = tcp_try_coalesce(sk, OOO_QUEUE, to, from, fragstolen);
4341
4342 /* In case tcp_drop() is called later, update to->gso_segs */
4343 if (res) {
4344 u32 gso_segs = max_t(u16, 1, skb_shinfo(to)->gso_segs) +
4345 max_t(u16, 1, skb_shinfo(from)->gso_segs);
4346
4347 skb_shinfo(to)->gso_segs = min_t(u32, gso_segs, 0xFFFF);
4348 }
4349 return res;
4350}

4352static void tcp_drop(struct sock *sk, struct sk_buff *skb)
4353{
4354 sk_drops_add(sk, skb);
4355 __kfree_skb(skb);
4356}

4358/* This one checks to see if we can put data from the
4359 * out_of_order queue into the receive_queue.
4360 */
4361static void tcp_ofo_queue(struct sock *sk)
4362{
4363 struct tcp_sock *tp = tcp_sk(sk);
4364 __u32 dsack_high = tp->rcv_nxt;
4365 bool fin, fragstolen, eaten;
4366 struct sk_buff *skb, *tail;
4367 struct rb_node *p;
4368
4369 p = rb_first(&tp->out_of_order_queue);
4370 while (p) {
4371 skb = rb_entry(p, struct sk_buff, rbnode);
4372 if (after(TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->seq, tp->rcv_nxt))
4373 break;
4374
4375 if (before(TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->seq, dsack_high)) {
4376 __u32 dsack = dsack_high;
4377 if (before(TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->end_seq, dsack_high))
4378 dsack_high = TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->end_seq;
4379 tcp_dsack_extend(sk, TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->seq, dsack);
4380 }
4381 p = rb_next(p);
4382 rb_erase(&skb->rbnode, &tp->out_of_order_queue);
4383 /* Replace tstamp which was stomped by rbnode */
4384 if (TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->has_rxtstamp)
4385 skb->tstamp = TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->swtstamp;
4386
4387 if (unlikely(!after(TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->end_seq, tp->rcv_nxt))) {
4388 SOCK_DEBUG(sk, "ofo packet was already received\n");
4389 tcp_drop(sk, skb);
4390 continue;
4391 }
4392 SOCK_DEBUG(sk, "ofo requeuing : rcv_next %X seq %X - %X\n",
4393 tp->rcv_nxt, TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->seq,
4394 TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->end_seq);
4395
4396 tail = skb_peek_tail(&sk->sk_receive_queue);
4397 eaten = tail && tcp_try_coalesce(sk, RCV_QUEUE,
4398 tail, skb, &fragstolen);
4399 tcp_rcv_nxt_update(tp, TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->end_seq);
4400 fin = TCP_SKB_CB(skb)->tcp_flags & TCPHDR_FIN;
4401 if (!eaten)
4402 __skb_queue_tail(&sk->sk_receive_queue, skb);
4403 else
4404 kfree_skb_partial(skb, fragstolen);
4405
4406 if (unlikely(fin)) {
4407 tcp_fin(sk);
4408 /* tcp_fin() purges tp->out_of_order_queue,
4409 * so we must end this loop right now.
4410 */
4411 break;
4412 }
4413 }
4414}

4416static bool tcp_prune_ofo_queue(struct sock *sk);
4417static int tcp_prune_queue(struct sock *sk);
